reviewTitle: Good for the price. A few important negatives...
reviewDescription: Watch is good enough for the price. But, after using it and observing certain realities for a day -1.) De-husked 4 coconuts manually using machete. On an average, it showed around 70 steps per coconut. Leading to an increase of 280 steps. Dehusking is a sitting/standing process. No walking involved.2.) Did around 2 hours if moving baby jellystones from one place to spread it over another area. Around 100 cubic feet of stones averagely. Maybe more, not less. Watch showed around 70 cal when I started work. After the work it showed 229 cal. Does it mean such heavy work consumes only around 150 cal? Strange. I thought it's much more than working out at the gym. For 2 hours. Involves loading jellystones with shovel, carrying, spreading it on another area covering around 350 sqft using shovel. This can be very misleading during gym visits and exercising, because it might lead to excessive workouts due to very low calorie burnt calculations. Can be dangerous for gym crazy people.3.) Battery can never ever stay 10 days. Manual inside the box says 7 days. Can never run 7 days also. Maximum it might give 2.5 days to 3 days of running. Do not expect more, practically. Maybe 4 days if you have less of calls and messages. WhatsApp, LinkedIn, FB and other notifications will drain the battery faster. Take care to choose notifications for apps that are really needed, to save battery.4.) After all the heavy duty work, it just shows 2 minutes of exercise üòÇ. Maybe this watch is not for a rural resident who has to do manual odd jobs too. Exercise, calories, and stress calculations do not work for real, physical hard work. Totally wrong calculations.5.) Heart rate, SpO2 are good. Also good for call notifications, messages and other social media notifications.6.) Request fitness enthusiasts to really cross verify calorie burnt calculations with other professionals before believing this watch statistics.Overall, no complaints really. Worth the price and the smartwatch has to be used responsibly and with awareness.

reviewTitle: A reliable product from the house of Titan
reviewDescription: Connecting the watch with my Android mobile phone was seamless, Expected a calculator and calendar in-built app, which is missing. The sensors are pretty good, There is no provision to lock/un-lock the watch, and I do not prefer to keep the Bluetooth connection on at all times, which might raise a privacy and security concern. Phone calls using the watch have crystal clear sound on speakers, no problem with the in-built mic either. The specification of the Feather Series "Fastrack Limitless FS1 Pro", is the same as the "FASTRACK REFLEX POWER" smartwatch listed on the official website, and the other variant is named "Fastrack Revoltt FS1 Pro". All have the same Model Number 38086PPxx. There was sometimes a slight lagging in the response of UI touch screen, the only gesture available is lift to wake, which acts instantly.
Features are really good. Very user friendly. Worth buying.. value for money.
